body: #10510 is another solution. Mutex is used. But since `grpc_timer_init` and `grpc_timer_cancel` are also using mutex, it should not have performance differences.

Adding a mutex with its paired operations is still fairly costly - I wouldn't see the having a mutex already in place as a waiver to add another one.

The sequence this PR is introducing might actually warrant some inline documentation, similar to https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/core/lib/iomgr/ev_epoll_linux.c#L162 - in fact, having an actual very explicit enum or list of #define with CAS operations used instead of the add might make this much more readable, and similar in performance.

If we're arguing about the cost of things, then it's time to create a
microbenchmark or two. Take a peek at bm_call_create for examples.
